Algiers 12-28 (AFP) - Former Algerian Prime Minister Mawloud Hamroush declared to Agence France Presse today, Monday, that he is a candidate for the early presidential elections in April 1999.
 
He said, "My nomination has been accepted and the official announcement remains to be made."

Yet, Hamroush explained that he will not officially declare his candidacy for a few days until after he has completed his consultations with prominent figures and with his "support committees" throughout the country.